Tirle: Spring REST Backend - Vendor CRUD API

This is a Spring Boot REST API application built as part of a hands-on learning series. It demonstrates the core concepts of building a backend service 
with clean architecture using Spring Boot, Spring Data JPA, and layered design patterns.

Project Overview

The project allows you to perform CRUD operations on Vendor data. It follows a clean, scalable architecture with clearly separated layers:

- Controller Layer: Handles HTTP requests
- Service Layer: Contains business logic
- Repository Layer: Manages database interactions using JPA
- Entity Layer: Represents database tables
- Exception Layer: Handles error cases gracefully

Tech Stack

- Java 17+
- Spring Boot
- Spring Web
- Spring Data JPA
- Maven
- MySQL / H2 (in-memory) Database
- IntelliJ IDEA
- Postman (for testing)

---
How to Run the Project Locally

 1. Clone the Repository

bash
git clone https://github.com/Bhanu-prakashcse/spring-rest-backend.git
cd spring-rest-backend

Folder structure:

spring-rest-backend/
├── src/
│   ├── main/
│   │   ├── java/
│   │   │   └── com/example/vendor/
│   │   │       ├── controller/
│   │   │       ├── service/
│   │   │       ├── repository/
│   │   │       ├── model/
│   │   │       └── exception/
│   │   └── resources/
│   │       └── application.properties
├── pom.xml
└── README.md
